o AH, Hermer A, Kern MSudden onset congestive heart failure with a continuous murmur: ruptured sinus of Valsalva aneurysm complicated by anomalous origin of the left coronary artery. <em>Cardiovasc Revasc Med</em> 2008;9(1):41–46.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.carrev.2007.08.008">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18206637/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Sudden+onset+congestive+heart+failure+with+a+continuous+murmur%3A+ruptured+sinus+of+Valsalva+aneurysm+complicated+by+anomalous+origin+of+the+left+coronary+artery&amp;author=AH+Seto&amp;author=A+Hermer&amp;author=M+Kern&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=Cardiovasc+Revasc+Med&amp;pages=41-46&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.carrev.2007.08.008&amp;pmid=18206637">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">65.</div><div id="b65-0300099" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Iida H, Sudo Y, Sunazawa T, Ukita HAcquired pseudoaneurysm of the sinus of Valsalva. <em>Tex Heart Inst J</em> 2008;35(2):186–188.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18612456/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Acquired+pseudoaneurysm+of+the+sinus+of+Valsalva&amp;author=H+Iida&amp;author=Y+Sudo&amp;author=T+Sunazawa&amp;author=H+Ukita&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=Tex+Heart+Inst+J&amp;pages=186-188&amp;pmid=18612456">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">66.</div><div id="b66-0300099" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Gonzalez JB, Koul S, Sawardekar U, et al.Images in cardiovascular medicine: sinus of Valsalva